'''Omi Shrine''' (乎彌神社, Omi Jinja) is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in {{ill|Nagahama|ja|長浜市}}, Yogo Town, Shiga Prefecture, Japan.

== Deities ==
* {{ill|Kochihito-no-Mikoto|ja|巨知人命}}
* {{ill|Watatsumi|ja|綿津見神}} (Sea God)
* {{ill|Nasitomi-no-Mikoto|ja|梨津臣命}} (worshipped at {{ill|Noimi Shrine|ja|乃弥神社}})

== Shrine crest ==
* Left Mitsudomoe (三つ巴)

== History ==
The shrine is traditionally said to have been founded during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Sujin|ja|崇神天皇}}. It is identified as the small shrine "Omi Jinja" mentioned in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyocho|ja|延喜式神名帳}} for {{ill|Ika District|ja|伊香郡}}, {{ill|Omi Province|ja|近江国}}, and is classified as a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社}} (disputed location).<ref>Other possible locations for the shrine include {{ill|Omi Shrine (Nagahama)|ja|大見神社}} in Kinomoto Town, Nagahama, and {{ill|Kasuga Shrine (Nagahama)|ja|春日神社 (長浜市高月町宇根)}} in Takatsuki Town, Nagahama.</ref> The shrine also enshrines the deities of the {{ill|Noimi Shrine|ja|乃弥神社}}, another {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社}}.

During the [[Meiji period]], four shrines within the shrine parish—Murakusa Shrine, Hachiman Shrine, Daimyojin Shrine, and Seki Shrine—were relocated to the shrine grounds. It was designated as a {{ill|Village shrine|ja|村社}} under the old shrine ranking system.

== Festivals ==
* Main Festival: April 8

== Auxiliary shrines ==
* {{ill|Murakusa Shrine|ja|村草神社}}
* {{ill|Hachiman Shrine|ja|八幡神社}}
* {{ill|Daimyojin Shrine|ja|大名持神社}}
* {{ill|Seki Shrine|ja|塞神社}}

