'''Omi Shrine''' (乎彌神社, Omi Jinja) is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in [[:en:Nagahama, Shiga|Nagahama]], Yogo Town, Shiga Prefecture, Japan.

== Deities ==
* {{ill|Kochihito-no-Mikoto|ja|巨知人命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kochihito-no-Mikoto|qq=}}
* {{ill|Watatsumi|ja|綿津見神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Watatsumi|qq=}} (Sea God)
* {{ill|Nasitomi-no-Mikoto|ja|梨津臣命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nasitomi-no-Mikoto|qq=}} (worshipped at {{ill|Noimi Shrine|ja|乃弥神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Noimi Shrine|qq=}})

== Shrine crest ==
* Left Mitsudomoe (三つ巴)

== History ==
The shrine is traditionally said to have been founded during the reign of [[:en:Emperor Sujin|Emperor Sujin]]. It is identified as the small shrine "Omi Jinja" mentioned in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}} for [[:en:Ika District, Shiga|Ika District]], [[:en:Ōmi Province|Omi Province]], and is classified as a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}} (disputed location).<ref>Other possible locations for the shrine include {{ill|Omi Shrine (Nagahama)|ja|大見神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Omi Shrine (Nagahama)|qq=}} in Kinomoto Town, Nagahama, and {{ill|Kasuga Shrine (Nagahama)|ja|春日神社 (長浜市高月町宇根)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kasuga Shrine (Nagahama)|qq=}} in Takatsuki Town, Nagahama.</ref> The shrine also enshrines the deities of the {{ill|Noimi Shrine|ja|乃弥神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Noimi Shrine|qq=}}, another {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}}.

During the [[Meiji period]], four shrines within the shrine parish—Murakusa Shrine, Hachiman Shrine, Daimyojin Shrine, and Seki Shrine—were relocated to the shrine grounds. It was designated as a {{ill|Village shrine|ja|村社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Village shrine|qq=}} under the old shrine Ranking system.

== Festivals ==
* Main Festival: April 8

